1
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:20,869
What's that, Mom?

2
00:00:23,548 --> 00:00:28,849
It's your dad's old shirt.
I found it in a trunk.

3
00:00:29,112 --> 00:00:31,530
See? It's still in good shape.

4
00:00:31,912 --> 00:00:33,814
So I'm giving it to you to wear.

5
00:00:35,184 --> 00:00:37,306
Later, if we sell the rice,

6
00:00:37,826 --> 00:00:42,737
I'll save some money
to buy you a new shirt in town.

7
00:00:50,038 --> 00:00:52,090
- Mom.
- Huh?

8
00:00:52,841 --> 00:00:54,292
I'm sorry.

9
00:00:56,264 --> 00:00:58,634
What are you apologizing for, Loy?

10
00:00:59,798 --> 00:01:00,803
Huh?

11
00:01:02,182 --> 00:01:03,192
Look.

12
00:01:05,592 --> 00:01:09,474
I... can't be a good son.

13
00:01:12,509 --> 00:01:14,629
I've never made you happy.

14
00:01:16,031 --> 00:01:17,401
I'm sorry.

15
00:01:18,121 --> 00:01:20,432
Hmm... Loy.

16
00:01:24,937 --> 00:01:25,966
Uh?

17
00:01:26,570 --> 00:01:28,853
Have you talked to Kaew yet?

18
00:01:30,349 --> 00:01:32,526
He's probably mad at you about something.

19
00:01:36,105 --> 00:01:37,255
How come, Mom?

20
00:01:38,685 --> 00:01:44,835
He probably thinks
I have feelings for his sister.

21
00:01:45,931 --> 00:01:47,188
What?

22
00:01:50,316 --> 00:01:52,907
You guys have known each
other since you were kids.

23
00:01:54,441 --> 00:01:58,645
He knows what kind of person you are, right?

24
00:02:00,109 --> 00:02:04,055
That's why he hates me.

25
00:02:05,476 --> 00:02:08,735
He probably thinks
Loy is trying to climb the social ladder.

26
00:02:10,312 --> 00:02:12,226
That I want to marry his sister.

27
00:02:16,689 --> 00:02:18,797
Why do you think that?

28
00:02:21,852 --> 00:02:23,591
Why wouldn't I think that, Mom?

29
00:02:24,924 --> 00:02:27,408
The reason Phaad messed with me,

30
00:02:28,728 --> 00:02:30,955
isn't it because Loy is poor?

31
00:02:32,639 --> 00:02:35,385
And the reason Kaew punched me,

32
00:02:36,030 --> 00:02:37,703
is because he's protective of his sister.

33
00:02:38,504 --> 00:02:40,444
Phaad's going to ask
for Whan's hand in marriage.

34
00:02:42,146 --> 00:02:45,593
The dowry will probably be huge.

35
00:02:46,181 --> 00:02:47,795
That's why he's so protective.

36
00:02:49,041 --> 00:02:52,320
He doesn't want her getting involved
with someone poor like me.

37
00:03:05,780 --> 00:03:07,268
I promise you, Mom.

38
00:03:09,940 --> 00:03:14,191
From now on, I won’t let anyone
look down on my mother ever again.

39
00:03:16,056 --> 00:03:17,457
I promise, Mom.

40
